emory, and fiction. In so doing, he reveals the innovative and sometimes troublesome ways in which authors can challenge or perpetuate gendered conventions of writing women's lives.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aArchetypes in literature. 0aMexican literaturey21st centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aSex role in literature. 0aWomen in literature. 0aWomen in popular culture. 0aWomenzMexicoxHistory. 4aCultural Studies : Cultural Studies. 4aGender and Sexuality : Gender Studies. 4aGender and Sexuality : Women's Studies. 4aLatin American, Caribbean, and Latinx Studies : Latin American Studies. 4aLiterature : Literary Criticism. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Caribbean & Latin American.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143847191440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438471914423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438471914/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles